http://archanaschangale.wordpress.com/2013/10/14/pig-installation-on-ubuntu/comment-page-1/
https://pig.apache.org/docs/r0.7.0/setup.html
https://www.inkling.com/read/hadoop-definitive-guide-tom-white-3rd/chapter-11/installing-and-running-pig

(Download Pig and unpack it)
http://pig.apache.org/releases.html#Download
($ export PATH=/<PigPath>/pig-0.12.1/bin:$PATH)
($ pig –help)
($ pig)

$ tar –xvf pig-0.12.1.tar.gz
$ sudo mkdir /home/hduser/pig
$ mv pig-0.12.1 /home/hduser/pig
$ cd ~
$ gedit ~/.bashrc

# paste 
export PIG_HOME=/home/hduser/pig
export PATH=$PATH:$PIG_HOME/bin
# end

(Restart the computer)

(Test the installation)
$ pig -h

----------------------------------------------------------------
[Running the Pig Scripts in Mapredue Mode]

(Start pig in mapreduce mode)
(move to the pigtmp directory)
(copy the Pig script file from pigtmp directpry to the HDFS directory)
$ hadoop fs -copyFromLocal exectite.log.bz2

(Set the HADOOP_CONF_DIR environment variable to the location of core-site.xml, hdfs-site.xml and mapred-site.xml)

$ java -cp $PIGDIR/pig.jar:$HADOOP_CONF_DIR org.apache.pig.Main script1-hadoop.pig

(Review the result files, located in the script1-hadoop-results HDFS directory)
$ hadoop fs -ls script1-hadoop-results
$ hadoop fs -cat 'script1-hadoop-results/*' | less
